\pard\qc\b\f1 Smart Campus Entry Monitoring System\par
\pard\qc\b\f1 Change Summary Report\par
\pard\qc\b0\f0 Generated for latest enhancement round\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 1. Overview\b0\f0\par
This document summarizes the changes implemented in the existing Smart Campus Entry Monitoring System without rebuilding the project. The work focused on two major feature areas:\par
\par
1. Warden-specific data restriction across dashboard, logs, and hosteller workflows.\par
2. Manual student creation support in Student Management, aligned with the Excel upload flow.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 2. Warden-Specific Data Restriction\b0\f0\par
\pard\b Feature Goal:\b0 Ensure that each warden can only access data related to the hostel assigned to them, while admin and security users continue to retain wider access.\par
\par
\pard\b Changes Implemented:\b0\par
1. Added an explicit hostel mapping field to the admin/staff model.\par
2. Updated staff registration and staff update logic to save the assigned hostel for warden accounts.\par
3. Added backend-level warden hostel scope resolution logic so access control is enforced even for direct API calls.\par
4. Updated dashboard APIs so a warden only receives student stats, hostel metrics, and hosteller views for their assigned hostel.\par
5. Updated entry log APIs so a warden only receives logs for students belonging to their assigned hostel.\par
6. Restricted unauthorized log actions for wardens.\par
7. Updated hosteller request APIs so wardens cannot view, approve, reject, or browse requests outside their assigned hostel.\par
8. Kept hostel assignment in sync between staff records and hostel records.\par
\par
\pard\b Backend Areas Updated:\b0\par
- Admin/staff model\par
- Auth controller and auth routes\par
- Hostel controller\par
- Dashboard controller\par
- Log controller\par
- Hosteller controller\par
- Shared warden scope service\par
\par
\pard\b Security Outcome:\b0\par
The restriction is now enforced at the backend level. Even if a warden manually calls the API, the system limits results to the hostel they are assigned to.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 3. Manual Student Add Form\b0\f0\par
\pard\b Feature Goal:\b0 Add a manual student creation flow in Student Management with the same functional behavior and downstream compatibility as the Excel upload system.\par
\par
\pard\b Changes Implemented:\b0\par
1. Added an Add Student button in the Student Management page.\par
2. Added a manual student form modal with all major student fields currently supported by the Excel workflow.\par
3. Included support for:\par
- SAP ID\par
- Name\par
- Email\par
- Phone\par
- Parent email\par
- Parent phone\par
- Category\par
- Course\par
- Department\par
- Year\par
- Address\par
- Blood group\par
- Hostel selection for hostellers\par
- Room number for hostellers\par
\par
4. Added category-driven hostel visibility so hostel fields appear only for hostellers.\par
5. Reused backend normalization logic so manually created students follow the same data shape as Excel-uploaded students.\par
6. Added request validation for manual student create and update operations.\par
7. Improved duplicate SAP ID and validation error handling for manual student creation.\par
8. Added a Create And Open Enrollment option so an admin can immediately continue into the existing enrollment flow after adding a student.\par
\par
\pard\b Consistency Outcome:\b0\par
Students created manually now behave like Excel-uploaded students in downstream features such as enrollment, logs, hostel workflows, and access tracking.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 4. Frontend Changes\b0\f0\par
\pard\b Pages Updated:\b0\par
1. Student Management\par
- Added Add Student button.\par
- Added full manual create modal.\par
- Preserved Excel upload support.\par
- Kept edit flow intact while aligning it more closely with the normalized backend payload.\par
\par
2. Enrollment\par
- Added support for preselecting a student after manual creation using query parameters.\par
\par
3. Settings\par
- Added hostel assignment support in staff management for warden accounts.\par
\par
4. Dashboard\par
- Adjusted the dashboard title and hostel filter behavior to better match warden-restricted access.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 5. Backend Changes\b0\f0\par
\pard\b Major Logic Updates:\b0\par
1. Added shared warden scope resolution service.\par
2. Added hostelId to admin/staff records.\par
3. Synced hostel assignment between wardens and hostel ownership records.\par
4. Restricted dashboard data at query level for wardens.\par
5. Restricted log data at query level for wardens.\par
6. Restricted hosteller request operations by assigned hostel.\par
7. Added manual student validation and more consistent student response payloads.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 6. Files Touched in This Change Set\b0\f0\par
Backend:\par
- backend/models/Admin.js\par
- backend/controllers/authController.js\par
- backend/routes/auth.js\par
- backend/controllers/hostelController.js\par
- backend/controllers/dashboardController.js\par
- backend/controllers/logController.js\par
- backend/controllers/hostellerController.js\par
- backend/controllers/studentController.js\par
- backend/routes/students.js\par
- backend/services/wardenScopeService.js\par
\par
Frontend:\par
- frontend/src/pages/Settings.jsx\par
- frontend/src/pages/StudentManagement.jsx\par
- frontend/src/pages/Enrollment.jsx\par
- frontend/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 7. Verification Notes\b0\f0\par
1. Backend syntax checks were completed successfully.\par
2. Backend modules loaded correctly after the changes.\par
3. Frontend build verification could not be fully completed in the sandbox because the Vite build process failed with a sandbox-related spawn EPERM error.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 8. Final Result\b0\f0\par
The system now supports secure warden-specific hostel access restrictions and a production-ready manual student entry workflow, while preserving existing behavior for admins, security staff, Excel upload, enrollment, and hostel operations.\par
\par
\pard\b\f1 End of Report\b0\f0\par
}
